  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1997-11-04", 
    "text": "Prevention of Truancy Act of 1997 - Directs the Secretary of Education to make demonstration grants for projects for the prevention or reduction of truancy, to partnerships consisting of an elementary school or secondary school, a local law enforcement agency, and a social service and youth serving organization. Gives grant priority to partnerships serving urban and rural areas with concentrations of poverty. Authorizes appropriations."
